# Backend .NET Rules

## Core System Integration

This project uses `core-system` as a git submodule. Shared modules:
- `Core.Common` -- base entities (`BaseEntity`, `IAuditableEntity`), `Result<T>` pattern, extensions
- `Core.Auth` -- session-based auth, RBAC with string permissions, rate limiting, audit middleware
- `Core.FileManagement` -- file upload/storage with SHA-256 deduplication
- `Core.Infrastructure` -- EF Core + PostgreSQL via Npgsql, entity configurations, SSE (`AddCoreSse`)

```csharp
// Permission checks use CoreAuthHelper
var check = await CoreAuthHelper.CheckPermissionAsync(HttpContext, _authService, "music:upload");
if (check is not null) return check;
```

## Controllers

- Thin controllers: inject service, call method, return result
- No business logic in controllers
- Routes: `[Route("api/[controller]")]` in kebab-case
- Return proper status codes: 200, 201, 204, 400, 401, 403, 404, 429
- Never resolve services via `HttpContext.RequestServices` -- use constructor injection only

## Services

- One interface + one implementation per service
- Interfaces live in `Services/Interfaces/`; implementations in `Services/`
- Services contain business logic; controllers do not
- All async methods MUST accept `CancellationToken cancellationToken = default` and propagate it to every downstream async call
- Never use `.Result` or `.Wait()` -- always `await`

## Workspace-Aware Queries

- All workspace-scoped entities (`PdfFile`, `Category`, `MergeList`, `CustomFilterGroup`) must be filtered by `WorkspaceId`
- Services receive `workspaceId` as a parameter -- never assume a default in the service layer
- Global entities (`Artist`) are shared across workspaces and do not filter by `WorkspaceId`

## EF Core

- Use `Include()` only when needed; avoid N+1
- Apply pagination on listings (`Skip`/`Take`)
- Use async methods (`ToListAsync`, `FirstOrDefaultAsync`) and pass `CancellationToken`
- Entity configurations via `IEntityTypeConfiguration<T>` or `ApplyCore*Entities()`

## Logging

- Use `ILogger<T>` with structured logging
- `Information` for business events, `Warning` for recoverable issues, `Error` for failures
- Never log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, PII)
- Format: `_logger.LogInformation("User {Username} created", username)`

## File Size Limits

- Controllers: max 200 lines
- Services: max 300 lines
- If exceeded, split into smaller units
